==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interferometer
<hw>In`ter*fe*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Interfere</er> and <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>An instrument for measuring small movements, distances, or
displacements by means of the interference of two beams of light; --
formerly also called also <altname>refractometer</altname>, but that
word now has a different meaning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

